> I repaired one of my front seats on the weekend.  My hat off to anyone
doing
> upholstery repair for a living.
>
> http://homepage.mac.com/mdelloca/PhotoAlbum7.html
>
>
> The old seats were down to springs and I got so used to it that I couldn't
> believe the difference at first.  I did discover that the original padding
> had foam sandwiched in between the horsehair (another VW special) which
the
> repros didn't have so the repro seat padding is probably firmer than the
> original.  I think they may last longer though before they disintegrate
into
> "tabacco".
>
> My final opinion: firm.
>
> I went with the horsehair because I'm a sucker for original and too many
> messages in the archive said that foam overstuffed the seat.  The
horsehair
> is a perfect fit especially if you are worrying about stressing the
original
> fabric.
